  - q: "What's the main difference between Forthglade and Butternut Box for a puppy?"
    a: "Format and feeding philosophy. Forthglade is cold-pressed dry food (plus wet trays) you keep in the cupboard — uniquely all-life-stage, so the same grain-free recipe carries from weaning to senior with no diet switches. Butternut Box is chilled fresh food, steam-cooked, delivered on subscription in pouches portioned to your puppy's exact weight and growth target. Forthglade wins on convenience and cost; Butternut Box wins on top-tier nutrition scores and hands-off portion control for growth."
  - q: "Which has the higher AADF rating, Forthglade or Butternut Box puppy?"
    a: "Butternut Box, on paper. Independent reviewer All About Dog Food rates Butternut Box around 93–94%, among the highest scores of any UK food, driven by 60% fresh meat and a clean steam-cooked recipe. Forthglade's cold-pressed dry sits at 73–75% and its wet trays at 77–88% — excellent for a cupboard food and well above typical puppy kibble, but a step below fresh. Both are genuinely strong; the gap reflects fresh-vs-dry format more than quality of intent."
