  - q: "Why does portion control matter so much for puppies?"
    a: "Because overfeeding a growing puppy — especially a large or giant breed — drives rapid growth that's linked to hip and elbow dysplasia and other developmental joint problems. Butternut Box's pre-portioned, weight-matched pouches make controlled growth almost automatic. With Forthglade you get the same result by weighing meals to the feeding guide and adjusting as your pup grows — it just takes a little more attention on your part."
  - q: "Can a puppy stay on the same food into adulthood?"
    a: "With Forthglade, yes — that's its standout feature. The same grain-free cold-pressed recipe is formulated for all life stages, so your pup never needs a stressful transition to adult food; you just adjust the quantity. Butternut Box also feeds adults and seniors, but it recalculates the recipe and portions as your dog matures, so the food evolves with them rather than staying identical. Either way you avoid the abrupt brand-switch most owners face."
  - q: "Which is better for a sensitive-stomach or fussy puppy?"
